ing careful not to crush them.","Place lemon juice and 100 g partially cooked berries in mixing bowl then blend <nobr>30 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> until smooth. Strain through a fine sieve pushing as much fruit through as possible.","While still warm, place juice and squeezed out gelatine in mixing bowl then stir <nobr>20 sec\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Leave to cool then pour sauce over remaining partially cooked blueberries. Cover and set aside."]},{"title":"Garnish","content":["Pipe a big blob of blueberry cream cheese at one end of a serving plate and drag a little using a spoon. Sprinkle crumble over and to one side. Place some blueberry compote at different positions and dot with blueberry juices. Dress with wood sorrel leaves. Serve with a scoop of yoghurt sorbet."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Blueberry Cream Cheese","content":["½ gelatine leaf","100 g blueberries","30 g caster sugar","¼ lemon, juice only","225 g cream cheese"]},{"title":"Yoghurt Sorbet","content":["1 gelatine leaf","120 g water","60 g caster sugar","50 g liquid glucose","600 g Greek yoghurt","10 g lemon juice"]},{"title":"Crumble","content":["125 g plain flour","50 g ground almonds","125 g unsalted butter, cut in pieces","75 g Demerara sugar","½ tsp ground cinnamon","½ tsp fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Blueberry Compote","content":["750 g blueberries, plus extra to garnish","100 g caster sugar","1 gelatine leaf","1 lemon, juice only"]},{"title":"Garnish","content":["40 leaves wood sorrel shoots or baby mint"]}],"id":"r178687","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/--V1KT1ABY9o\/XZWfaUOjkaI\/AAAAAAAAfEE\/7BK41GB7P9MLugoHm8VW8w_HfmzSs9-ZwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_udArEhmQfVUcPPdJ.png","title":"Blueberry Cheesecake, Yoghurt Sorbet","publishedAt":"2017-10-09T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13 g","fat":"29 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"65 g","calories":"2433 kJ \/ 581 kcal"},"usefulItems":"fine sieve, cling film, baking paper, baking tray and baking paper, wire rack, airtight container, saucepan, mediu